related_questions.question: What does it mean to be affiliated with a company?
related_questions.snippet: Two companies are affiliated when one company owns less than a majority of the voting stock of the other, usually less than 50%, or when both are subsidiaries of a third corporation. A subsidiary is a company where more than 50% of the voting shares are owned by another corporation, called the parent company.

related_questions.question: What is the difference between affiliated and associated?
related_questions.snippet: As nouns the difference between affiliate and associate is that affiliate is someone or something that is affiliated, or associated; a member of a group of associated things while associate is a person united with another or others in an act, enterprise, or business; a partner or colleague.

related_questions.question: What does not affiliated mean?
related_questions.snippet: Being affiliated usually means having an association with, or connection to someone, or something. So being not affiliated means that you do not have any association or connection to a particular person, organisation or thing. Please buy a good dictionary.Aug 13, 2016
